                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89 Great Britain/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-07-17T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1922—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 17—7:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>295. The Embassy is officially informed by the Foreign Office that a special
                    delegation will proceed to the United States early in September to negotiate
                    terms for the funding of the British debt to the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
